  "content": {
    "title": "CEA vs CAS: Choosing Between Carotid Endarterectomy and Carotid Artery Stenting",
    "definition": "Evidence-based comparison of carotid endarterectomy (CEA) and carotid artery stenting (CAS) for treatment of carotid stenosis, incorporating patient-specific factors, anatomic considerations, and trial data to guide treatment selection.",
